          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇸🇦 Saudi Arabia:</strong>    
          French President Emmanuel Macron and Saudi Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman signed a strategic <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20241203-macron-and-saudi-crown-prince-sign-partnership-deal-call-for-lebanon-elections" target="_blank">partnership</a> in Riyadh, focusing on defense, energy transition, and regional stability, including Lebanon. They supported presidential elections in Lebanon and the fragile ceasefire with Israel. Macron’s visit coincided with his domestic political challenges and escalating Middle East tensions. France seeks Saudi support for Lebanon’s army and broader reforms to stabilize its economy. Both leaders called for a Gaza ceasefire and a two-state Israeli-Palestinian solution. Macron’s delegation included major French companies aiming to bolster economic ties, discussing potential Saudi purchases of French Rafale fighter jets.</p>
        </mj-text>
