          UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer <a href="https://www.politico.eu/article/keir-starmer-britain-uk-doesnt-have-to-pick-between-donald-trump-us-and-europe/" target="_blank">emphasized</a> that Britain need not choose between its alliances with the United States and Europe, advocating for strong ties with both in a major speech on foreign policy. Starmer reaffirmed the enduring “special relationship” with America while pursuing improved post-Brexit relations with the EU by addressing potential tensions with the Trump-led U.S., including looming tariffs and NATO funding concerns. Starmer also addressed the Ukraine war, underscoring continued support to ensure Kyiv’s strength in future peace negotiations.</p>
