          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:16px !important">How many countries have the death penalty?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-4-3.jpg" alt="How many countries have the death penalty?" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">As of 2024, <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/world-45835584" target="_blank">55 countries worldwide</a> still retain the death penalty in law and practice, while 28 more have it in law but have not carried out executions in at least 10 years, effectively observing a moratorium. This leaves a majority of countries having abolished the death penalty entirely for all crimes, reflecting a global trend toward abolition.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Regions differ significantly in their approach. For example, most European and Latin American nations have abolished it, while countries in the Middle East, parts of Asia, and Africa still actively enforce it. Notable countries like the United States, China, Iran, and Saudi Arabia frequently carry out executions, often sparking international debate about human rights and justice.​</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Organizations like <a href="https://www.amnesty.org/en/what-we-do/death-penalty/#:~:text=Amnesty%20International%20holds%20that%20the,by%20the%20UN%20in%201948." target="_blank">Amnesty International</a> and the United Nations oppose this practice and argue for its abolition worldwide due to <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/ethics/capitalpunishment/against_1.shtml" target="_blank">concerns</a> over human rights violations, fairness, and effectiveness as a deterrent. <a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/ethics/capitalpunishment/for_1.shtml" target="_blank">Supporters</a> believe it is a just punishment for heinous crimes and the only way to bring justice to the victims.​</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
